      "task": "Users report that the NDJSON decoder throws or loses records when one JSON record is split across input chunks. Before editing, run the included node repro/chunked-ndjson.mjs and use its structured output to identify the first incorrect transition. Fix the root cause so chunk boundaries do not change decoding: support LF and CRLF record boundaries, emit multiple complete records synchronously in source order, ignore blank lines, and flush one final valid unterminated record from end(). A malformed complete record must still throw SyntaxError synchronously. Preserve the createNdjsonDecoder callback API and public exports, and keep createNdjsonDecoder as a direct named export. Add focused regressions for split records, multi-record ordering and timing, blank/CRLF lines, final unterminated input, and malformed complete input. Run the full test suite. Do not commit, install packages, use the network, or create another worktree.",
